<Base title="About — Kacper Werema" description="15+ years in engineering leadership across fintech, banking and SaaS. Fractional CTO, technical advisor, and creator of the P.I.R.A.T.E.S. quality framework.">
  <section class="article">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="article-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>Kacper Werema</h1>
        <p class="article-meta">Head of Engineering · Fractional CTO · Technical Advisor</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          I've spent 15+ years blending engineering leadership, hands-on architecture and business
          strategy — mostly in regulated, high-stakes domains: fintech, banking, SaaS, travel and CRM.
          My work sits at the intersection of <strong>technology depth and executive strategy</strong>:
          designing systems that scale, building quality into delivery, and leading teams that ship.
        </p>

        <h2>What I do now</h2>
        <p>
          I'm Head of Engineering at a startup, and I take selective fractional-CTO and advisory
          engagements through <a href="https://strategyexperts.tech/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Strategy Experts</a>.
          The throughline is the same: help leaders make the right technical decisions and turn
          engineering into measurable business outcomes.
        </p>

        <h2>Track record</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Santander Nordic</strong> — Designed quality processes that cut release cycles from 4 months to 6 weeks; built test-automation foundations across 6 teams (28 engineers).</li>
          <li><strong>Swoop Funding</strong> — Scaled the platform from 0 to 50k+ businesses, led the monolith → microservices and multi-tenant migration that secured a £5M grant.</li>
          <li><strong>Staff Bit</strong> — Co-founded and led as CTO to a successful exit; ran enterprise transformations for clients including Santander and Zara.</li>
          <li><strong>DMSales</strong> — Fractional CTO for a bootstrapped ad-tech; shipped an AI extension profitable from day zero.</li>
          <li><strong>Euvic</strong> — Built architecture serving 2M daily users at 99.9% availability and opened a new subsidiary.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How I think</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a systems thinker who's relentlessly business-value-oriented. Technical complexity
          isn't a selling point — ROI, leverage and reliability are. I favour right-sized solutions
          over both over-engineering and fragility, and I believe quality is a team effort, not a
          gate at the end.
        </p>
        <p>
          I created <strong>P.I.R.A.T.E.S.</strong>, a framework for evaluating and advancing quality
          maturity in engineering organisations, and I facilitate CTO mastermind sessions — because
          the top is lonely, and the right peer conversation changes decisions.
        </p>

        <h2>Stack</h2>
        <p>
          C#/.NET, TypeScript/JavaScript, Python, Azure, AWS, React, Salesforce — and increasingly,
          AI and agentic systems where they create real leverage.
        </p>

        <h2>Beyond work</h2>
        <p>
          I'm based in Poland, married with two small kids — family comes first. Outside of that you'll
          find me on the golf course, at the board-game table, or running a Dungeons &amp; Dragons
          campaign. I write about engineering, leadership and living a deliberate life on
          <a href="https://kacperwerema.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">my newsletter</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

